HEADWORD: Boucherize
<hw>Bou"cher*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[After Dr.
Auguste <etsep>Boucherie</etsep>, a French chemist, who invented the
process.]</ety> <def>To impregnate with a preservative solution of
copper sulphate, as timber, railroad ties, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boud</ent>⟦br⟧
